                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>There are jobs that even the handiest of homeowners should leave to a licensed professional. Furnace repairs fall into this category.</p> </div>
                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Even if it’s a minor repair, you should always entrust the task to a qualified HVAC technician from East Side Ventilation. Here are the risks you’re exposing yourself to when attempting to do it yourself.</p><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Carbon Monoxide Poisoning</span><br>If you have an oil or gas furnace, attempting DIY repairs comes with the risk of causing a carbon monoxide leak. This poisonous gas is a by-product of combustion processes and kills hundreds of people every year. It’s also odourless, tasteless and colourless, making it nearly impossible to detect unless you have a carbon monoxide detector. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Fire</span><br>The other major risk you run when attempting repairs on your furnace is that of sparking a fire. Electric wiring and gas lines are common causes of house fires and it takes years of training to know how to safely repair and handle them. If your furnace isn’t working well, call a professional as soon as you can. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Electric Shock</span><br>Something as simple as a shorted wire can cause serious injury or even death. The average homeowner lacks the training and tools to safely inspect and repair their furnace’s electric components. In fact, you should always hire a licensed and certified professional to deal with any and all electrical work.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Voided Warranty</span><br>Issues with you furnace are often covered under your manufacturer’s warranty. However, if anyone other than a licensed professional performs repairs on the appliance, the warranty may be automatically voided. <br><br>Think twice about performing even minor repairs to your furnace. A mistake could cost you dearly. Keeping the warranty valid can mean the difference between paying out-of-pocket for a brand-new furnace and having the manufacturer cover the cost.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Professional Furnace Repair in Winnipeg</span><br>If you need your furnace repaired, count on the experienced heating technicians at East Side Ventilation. We’re qualified to fix gas, electric and even geothermal heating systems and provide <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-repair-replacement-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">24/7 emergency repair services</a>. We also provide furnace <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-installation-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">installation</a>, <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-service-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">tune-up</a> and <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-cleaning-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">cleaning services</a>. To schedule an appointment, or to learn more about our Winnipeg HVAC services, <a href="/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">get in touch</a> with us today.</div>
